==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*loga-'', from Indo-European ''*legh-''. Cognate with Old Frisian [[loch|lōch]], Old High German [[luog]]. The IE root is also the source of Greek [[λεκτρον]], Latin [[lectus]] ‘bed’, Celtic ''*leg-'' (Old Irish [[lige]], Irish [[luighe]]), Slavic ''*ležati'' (Russian [[лежать]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/lo:ç/}}

===Noun===
'''lōg''' {{n}}
# a [[place]], [[stead]]
#:''on his log'': in his place; instead of him.

====Related words====
*[[licgan]]
*[[lecgan]]
*[[leger#Old English|leġer]]
*[[geliger|ġeliġer]]

[[Category:Old English nouns]]

